Air Peace, said it would commence flights from Lagos and Abuja to Ilorin, the Kwara State capital on June 17. The airline hinted that it had equally increased Accra flight frequency. Spokesperson for the airline, Stanley Olisa, disclosed this to journalists on Monday. He stated that the airline is set to kick off daily Abuja-Ilorin-Abuja and Lagos-Ilorin-Lagos flights on June 17, 2021. “The flying public can start booking on our website and mobile app”, he said. He added that the airline has also increased its Accra flights to two, daily in line with popular demand. “Air Peace currently services 16 domestic routes, 5 regional routes and 2 international destinations including Johannesburg and boasts of a mixed fleet of 28 aircraft, including 2 brand new Embraer 195-E2 jets delivered earlier this year, with 11 more lined up for delivery,” he said. 